  "text": "MAX{I (x;x),I (y;y)} for mining quantitative correlated patterns. This definition is symmetric, since a correlated pattern requires all attributes in the pattern be strongly correlated, while normalized mutual information in this paper is directional because a QAR is an implication of the antecedent on the consequent. We emphasize that the work in this paper and the work in Ke et al. [CITATION_1] are complementary to each other, since correlated patterns are in fact originally proposed as a complement to association rules. While the focus in Ke et al. [CITATION_2] is to mine patterns with strongly correlated items, the contribution of this paper is to obtain the implication of one quantitative pattern on the high probability of the occurrence of another pattern, which is different from the scope of Ke et al. [CITATION_3] ",
